  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: 1.70\r\nOS & Version: Ubuntu 16.04\r\n\r\nIt would be great to have an easy way to change where the ethereum data chain is stored. You could prompt during installation, and also allow changing from within the app. I am running a modest cpu and the OS is on a flash drive. The flash drive is small, so I have a big external drive for my chaindata.\r\n",
